{"type":"section","nativeType":"section","number":"2519","heading":"Prevention of and response to hazing and bullying","label":"2519 Prevention of and response to hazing and bullying","identifier":"/us/usc/t14/s2519","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t14/stII/ch25/schI","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft14%2Fs2519","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":["Editorial Notes","References in TextSection 549 of the National Defense Authorization Act for Fiscal Year 2017, referred to in subsec. (a), is , which is set out as a note under , Armed Forces.section 549 of Pub. L. 114–328section 113 of Title 10The Uniform Code of Military Justice, referred to in subsec. (c)(9)(E), is chapter 47 (§ 801 et seq.) of Title 10, Armed Forces."],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"a","heading":".—Anti-hazing and Anti-bullying Database","label":"a .—Anti-hazing and Anti-bullying Database","identifier":"/us/usc/t14/s2519/a","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t14/s2519","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft14%2Fs2519%2Fa","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The Secretary of the department in which the Coast Guard is operating, in consultation with the Secretary of Defense, shall cooperate in the establishment and use of a comprehensive and consistent data-collection system described in section 549 of the National Defense Authorization Act for Fiscal Year 2017 ( note) for the collection of reports, including anonymous reports, of incidents of hazing or bullying.10 U.S.C. 113","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"b","heading":".—Improved Training","label":"b .—Improved Training","identifier":"/us/usc/t14/s2519/b","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t14/s2519","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft14%2Fs2519%2Fb","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The Commandant shall seek to improve training to assist members of the Coast Guard to better recognize, prevent, and respond to hazing and bullying at all command levels.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"c","heading":".—Annual Reports on Hazing and Bullying","label":"c .—Annual Reports on Hazing and Bullying","identifier":"/us/usc/t14/s2519/c","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t14/s2519","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft14%2Fs2519%2Fc","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t14/s2519/c/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t14/s2519/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft14%2Fs2519%2Fc%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t14/s2519/c/1/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t14/s2519/c/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft14%2Fs2519%2Fc%2F1%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"to prevent and to respond to incidents of hazing or bullying involving members of the Coast Guard;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t14/s2519/c/1/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t14/s2519/c/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft14%2Fs2519%2Fc%2F1%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"to track and encourage reporting, including reporting anonymously, incidents of hazing in the Coast Guard; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"C","heading":null,"label":"C","identifier":"/us/usc/t14/s2519/c/1/C","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t14/s2519/c/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft14%2Fs2519%2Fc%2F1%2FC","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"to ensure the consistent implementation of anti-hazing and anti-bullying policies.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t14/s2519/c/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t14/s2519/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft14%2Fs2519%2Fc%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"A discussion of the policies of the Coast Guard for preventing and responding to incidents of hazing.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"3","heading":null,"label":"3","identifier":"/us/usc/t14/s2519/c/3","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t14/s2519/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft14%2Fs2519%2Fc%2F3","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"A description of comprehensive data collection systems of the Coast Guard for collecting hazing or bullying reports involving a member of the Coast Guard.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"4","heading":null,"label":"4","identifier":"/us/usc/t14/s2519/c/4","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t14/s2519/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft14%2Fs2519%2Fc%2F4","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"A description of processes of the Coast Guard to identify, document, and report alleged instances of hazing or bullying. Such description shall include the methodology the Coast Guard uses to categorize and count potential instances of hazing or bullying.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"5","heading":null,"label":"5","identifier":"/us/usc/t14/s2519/c/5","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t14/s2519/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft14%2Fs2519%2Fc%2F5","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"A description of any training provided to members of the Coast Guard on recognizing and preventing hazing.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"6","heading":null,"label":"6","identifier":"/us/usc/t14/s2519/c/6","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t14/s2519/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft14%2Fs2519%2Fc%2F6","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t14/s2519/c/6/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t14/s2519/c/6","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft14%2Fs2519%2Fc%2F6%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the number of alleged and substantiated incidents of hazing involving members of the Coast Guard;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t14/s2519/c/6/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t14/s2519/c/6","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft14%2Fs2519%2Fc%2F6%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"a description of the nature of each such incident; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"C","heading":null,"label":"C","identifier":"/us/usc/t14/s2519/c/6/C","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t14/s2519/c/6","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft14%2Fs2519%2Fc%2F6%2FC","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"a description of the actions taken to address each such incident through nonjudicial and judicial actions.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"7","heading":null,"label":"7","identifier":"/us/usc/t14/s2519/c/7","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t14/s2519/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft14%2Fs2519%2Fc%2F7","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t14/s2519/c/7/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t14/s2519/c/7","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft14%2Fs2519%2Fc%2F7%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the quality of such training;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t14/s2519/c/7/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t14/s2519/c/7","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft14%2Fs2519%2Fc%2F7%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the need for modifications to such training; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"C","heading":null,"label":"C","identifier":"/us/usc/t14/s2519/c/7/C","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t14/s2519/c/7","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft14%2Fs2519%2Fc%2F7%2FC","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the need to require additional such training.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"8","heading":null,"label":"8","identifier":"/us/usc/t14/s2519/c/8","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t14/s2519/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft14%2Fs2519%2Fc%2F8","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t14/s2519/c/8/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t14/s2519/c/8","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft14%2Fs2519%2Fc%2F8%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the effectiveness of the Coast Guard in tracking and reporting instances of hazing or bullying; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t14/s2519/c/8/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t14/s2519/c/8","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft14%2Fs2519%2Fc%2F8%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"whether the performance of the Coast Guard with respect to such tracking and reporting was satisfactory or unsatisfactory during the preceding fiscal year.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"9","heading":null,"label":"9","identifier":"/us/usc/t14/s2519/c/9","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t14/s2519/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft14%2Fs2519%2Fc%2F9","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t14/s2519/c/9/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t14/s2519/c/9","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft14%2Fs2519%2Fc%2F9%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the policies described in paragraph (4) ;1So in original. Probably should be “paragraph (2)”.1","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t14/s2519/c/9/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t14/s2519/c/9","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft14%2Fs2519%2Fc%2F9%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the comprehensive data collection systems described in paragraph (5) ;2So in original. Probably should be “paragraph (3)”.2","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"C","heading":null,"label":"C","identifier":"/us/usc/t14/s2519/c/9/C","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t14/s2519/c/9","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft14%2Fs2519%2Fc%2F9%2FC","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the processes described in paragraph (6) ;3So in original. Probably should be “paragraph (4)”.3","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"D","heading":null,"label":"D","identifier":"/us/usc/t14/s2519/c/9/D","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t14/s2519/c/9","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft14%2Fs2519%2Fc%2F9%2FD","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the training described in paragraph (9) ; and4So in original. Probably should be “paragraph (5)”.4","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"E","heading":null,"label":"E","identifier":"/us/usc/t14/s2519/c/9/E","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t14/s2519/c/9","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft14%2Fs2519%2Fc%2F9%2FE","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the Uniform Code of Military Justice or the Manual for Courts-Martial to improve the prosecution of persons alleged to have committed hazing or bullying in the Coast Guard.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"10","heading":null,"label":"10","identifier":"/us/usc/t14/s2519/c/10","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t14/s2519/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft14%2Fs2519%2Fc%2F10","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The status of efforts of the Commandant to evaluate the prevalence of hazing and bullying in the Coast Guard.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"11","heading":null,"label":"11","identifier":"/us/usc/t14/s2519/c/11","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t14/s2519/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft14%2Fs2519%2Fc%2F11","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"Data on allegations of hazing and bullying in the Coast Guard, including final disposition of investigations.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"12","heading":null,"label":"12","identifier":"/us/usc/t14/s2519/c/12","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t14/s2519/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft14%2Fs2519%2Fc%2F12","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"Plans of the Commandant to improve hazing and bullying prevention and response during the next reporting year.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]}]}
